Definition
RCZ (Resonant Containment Zone): The dynamic boundary region where emergent shards condense. It is the lawful zone in which photons (as Emergence Operators) and leptons (as Containment Operators) interact to stabilize new Dâ‚ƒ volumes.

Core Functions
